/*ğŸ§© Question:
Write a SystemVerilog function that takes an integer dynamic array and
returns the reversed version of that array.

ğŸ§  Requirements:
Use a function.

Donâ€™t use the built-in .reverse() method.

Manually swap elements using a loop.

Return the reversed array.


module tb;
int arr[]='{1,4,7,9};
int p[];
function automatic void rev(ref int x[],output int rev_arr[]);
int q[];
int k;
k=x.size();
q=new[k];
for(int i=0;i<x.size();i++)
begin
q[i]=x[x.size()-1-i];
end
rev_arr=q;
endfunction

initial
begin
rev(arr,p);
$display("arr=%p,p=%p",arr,p);
end
endmodule

output:arr='{1, 4, 7, 9} ,p='{9, 7, 4, 1}

  
